{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, Pengi [32] demonstrates how frozen LLMs can be prompted using projected speech embeddings to perform a variety of tasks.",
    "Subsequent works like SALMONN [26], Qwen-Audio [37], and OSUM [33] further extend this design to support broad speech understanding and multimodal reasoning tasks.Continuous modeling has proven particularly effective for applications requiring fine-grained acoustic discrimination, including ASR [31], ST [63].",
    "Models like FireRedASR [31] and LLAST [63] show that state-of-the-art performance can be achieved with minimal architectural modification.",
    "In many cases, a simple projection layer is sufficient, together with limited fine-tuning [27], [30].Although this paradigm can achieve high accuracy in specific tasks, it also introduces certain challenges.",
    "When the amount of training data or task diversity is limited, the model is prone to overfitting [64], [65]."
  ]
}